init_text:
How Do You Think Technology Affects Dating?

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: That way I can see their actual personality, react to their facial expressions and hand gestures, and just immediately feel if there is a connection or not.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And there is also the possibility to be catfished, which can seem more real.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Over text or on social media, we are limited in what we can convey and what we can hear from that person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: People tend to be more dorky or boring or awkward over technology than they are in person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think technology is great for keeping in touch with someone you already know and love.
